  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is documented on all but one validation result (an internal mesh-sensitivity study treated as purely deterministic). The package is accepted following review by the credibility assessment team. Embedded adversarial conditions: (a) the bound Claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance link (W-EP-01, Critical); (b) one ValidationResult omits hasUncertaintyQuantification (W-AL-01, High), triggering a COMPOUND-01 compound-risk annotation.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-vad",
