      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index absolute value comparison — clinical operating range",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements across 5 flow-speed combinations. All predictions fall within experimental measurement uncertainty bands. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation on blood viscosity and pump speed inputs yields 90% prediction intervals fully below the clinical threshold of 0.005 g/100 L.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/mc-hemolysis-index-5op",
        "type": "UncertaintyQuantification",
        "method": "Monte Carlo",
