    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for MRL 5 Class III device context. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed across primary validation results. Validation metric U_val satisfied for all decision-critical QoIs. The deterministic mesh sensitivity study (VR-003) does not require stochastic UQ per team interpretation of ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3.2, as it is a verification rather than validation activity. Independent peer review completed with no outstanding findings. Credibility assessment team concludes the CFD model is sufficiently credible for its intended use in predicting absolute hemolysis levels for the VAD COU.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
